--- !u!114 &1798988481
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1798988473}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 993eafc72c6a68c4a830a8b83500dccc, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  hackerPanel: {fileID: 45023171}
  hackerDisplayText: {fileID: 2002116275}
  conversationSteps:
  - hackerStatement: Hello, Paul! How are you?
    option1: Um. Hello?
    option2: How did you know my name?
    option3: Who are you?
    response1: You sound nervous. You should be. Sitting in that chair carries a
      heavy price, and the interest is starting to collect.
    response2: "I know more than just your name. I know your employee ID, your shift
      hours, and exactly which files or emails you\u2019ve been \"cleaning\" for
      the Mayor."
    response3: A ghost. Or a warning. It depends entirely on what you do with the
      terminal.
  - hackerStatement: I used to sit where you are sitting now. I drank from that same
      mug. I even left a note under the desk. Did you find it, Paul?
    option1: You are Clerk Reyes?
    option2: Why did you leave?
    option3: What happened to you?
    response1: Reyes is the name of a man who doesn't exist anymore. Call me a whistleblower.
      Or call me the guy who didn't want to drown with the rest of this town.
    response2: I didn't "leave." I was escorted out. The Mayor doesn't like it when
      his clerks start asking why the flood walls in Brgy. Matapang are made of sand
      instead of concrete.
    response3: They offered me a "vacation." I haven't seen the sun in months. The
      Mayor doesn't fire people; he erases them to keep the ledger clean.
  - hackerStatement: "The Mayor is a generous man, isn't he? Paying for your mother\u2019s
      heart surgery at that private hospital... it must feel like a miracle for your
      family."
    option1: He is a good man for doing that.
    option2: How do you know about her?
    option3: "It\u2019s none of your business."
    response1: '"Good" isn''t the word I''d use. "Calculated" is better. He didn''t
      give you a gift; he bought a leash. He owns you now.'
    response2: "Every hospital bill in this district goes through the Mayor\u2019s
      \"Special Discretionary Fund.\" I've seen the receipts. Your mother's life
      is being traded for your silence."
    response3: It becomes my business when her surgery is funded by money stolen
      from the Brgy. Matulungin drainage project. Her life for twelve others who
      will die in the next flood. Fair trade?
  - hackerStatement: Look at the file 'AGOS_PHASE_2'. It claims 50 million pesos
      was spent on the dike in Brgy. Matapang. Go on. Open it. Tell me what you see.
    option1: '[Open File] It looks like a standard ledger.'
    option2: I am not supposed to look at Phase 2.
    option3: What are you trying to prove?
    response1: "Look at the contractor. 'Vocolith Construction.' It\u2019s a ghost
      company owned by the Mayor\u2019s cousin. That 50 million bought a private
      resort, not a dike."
    response2: "Because if you do, you\u2019ll realize the \"dike\" is just a pile
      of dirt covered in grass. It will wash away the second the storm hits."
    response3: "I\u2019m proving that the people of Brgy. Matapang are being left
      to die so the Mayor can keep his campaign pockets full. You are the one helping
      him hide the evidence."
  - hackerStatement: The clouds are getting dark over the valley. The weather bureau
      says the storm will hit by morning. Thousands of families in Brgy. Matapang
      are sleeping, thinking they are safe behind a wall that doesn't exist.
    option1: What can I even do?
    option2: I can't stop the rain.
    option3: I have to protect my mother first.
    response1: Leak the Phase 2 ledger. Send it to the news stations. Force the Mayor
      to open the emergency spillways before the pressure breaks the dirt walls.
    response2: You can't stop the rain, but you can stop the lies. If they know the
      dike is a sham, they can evacuate. If you stay silent, they will drown in their
      beds.
    response3: "And that is exactly what the Mayor is counting on. He knows you\u2019ll
      choose your own blood over the lives of an entire barangay. He\u2019s using
      your love as a weapon."
  - hackerStatement: "Careful, Paul. I just saw the security guard walk past your
      door. He\u2019s looking at his watch. You\u2019re staying late tonight. He\u2019s
      getting suspicious."
    option1: Is he working for the Mayor?
    option2: I'm just doing my job.
    option3: Help me get out of here.
    response1: Everyone in this building works for the Mayor. The janitor, the guard,
      even the water guy. They are all eyes. And right now, they are watching you.
    response2: Your "job" was supposed to be public service. Now your job is evidence
      disposal. Don't confuse the two before it's too late.
    response3: I can't help you leave, but I can help you survive the night. Keep
      the terminal window small. Don't look at the cameras. If you see the red light
      blink twice, it means they are recording.
  - hackerStatement: This is my last transmission before the system locks down for
      the night. Tomorrow, the Mayor will come to your desk. He will look you in
      the eye and ask if the files are gone. He will mention your mother again.
    option1: I'm scared of what he'll do.
    option2: I'll do what I have to do.
    option3: Why did you choose to tell me?
    response1: Good. Fear means you still have a conscience. Use it to make the right
      choice when the water starts rising.
    response2: '"What you have to do" could mean saving the town or saving your own
      skin. Just remember: once you hit ''Delete'' on those logs, you are a "Kasabwat"
      forever.'
    response3: 'Because you''re the one holding the key. You''re the one the system
      chose to replace me. I''m giving you the chance I never had: a way to walk
      away with a clean heart.'
